<br>
Thanks you very much for a great Summit! By all accounts it was a huge success. I can speak for the EverQuest Development Team and tell you that we're all grateful for the input you provided. In fact, in trying to generate this list to give to you this evening, we realized there was so much to go over that we wouldn't be able to get a complete list togather in time. We're committed to not only listening to your feedback, but working with you to make EverQuest more enjoyable for yours to come.<br>
<br>
So, we decided to list the Top Ten themes we would address starting Monday, as well as the most common themes that we'll come back with more information on by mid-week next week.<br>
<br>
A quick discussion resulted in a list of items that we will immediatly address:<br>
<br>
-Add scripting to shut off empty instances of Plane of Time<br>
-Raid message of the day<br>
-Improving how we handle beta and the testing process<br>
-Increase the number of debuffs allowed on MOBs<br>
-Increase buffs on players thru AA's<br>
-Note field on raid window<br>
-Improved consent &amp; drag for raid, group and guild<br>
-Improve corpse drag radius<br>
-Make charms not no-drop<br>
-Guild and individual rewards for guild beta testing<br>
-Work on larger To Do List... I know this is a little random<br>
<br>
Future items we will immediately begin looking at and discussing are as follows:<br>
<br>
-Plane of Time instancing and other issues<br>
-back flagging solutions to help with high end guild atrophy<br>
-Improve raid and guild functionality<br>
-Auto loot all for your corpse<br>
-Improvements to Raid XP<br>
-No more alien NPC's (focusing more on familiar norrathian themes)<br>
-Solo LDoN-Style instances or similar content<br>
-Issues with item augmentations<br>
-Possible enhancement to Guild Wars<br>
<br>
Of course these aren't all of the itmes. You brought us a CD, 2 Books, 20 printed sheets of a manifesto. We'll need to go through all of those and our notes before we can really get a good tally of all of the wonderful ideas and questions that were presented.<br>
<br>
Thank you again for your feedback and participation. We've had a greatd weekend and a wonderful display of things to come.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
EverQuest Development Team <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=565636" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/soteq/aurron2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=espioidsavant>Espio Idsavant</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lanys.evercrest.com/user-images/966/biggrinjester.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#330000>(6/6/04 8:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://lanys.evercrest.com/user-images/966/eqpa-espleave-mini2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letter from SoE from Summit</span><hr size=1> Sounds like some good stuff.<br>
